<i>-Who is he?</i>
<i>-Who is he?</i>

2:06:38.583 --> 2:06:41.500
HAIL LORD SHIVA

2:06:54.958 --> 2:06:55.791
Brother.

2:06:57.625 --> 2:06:59.875
<i>Come, leave your slippers here,</i>
<i>buy some flowers and go.</i>

2:07:03.833 --> 2:07:05.208
Why, brother?
After coming this close,

2:07:05.291 --> 2:07:06.791
you're going back
without going inside the temple?

2:07:09.291 --> 2:07:11.333
Brother, it's okay
if you don't buy flowers,

2:07:11.416 --> 2:07:12.666
but just go inside,
and offer your prayers.

2:07:12.750 --> 2:07:13.833
It's an auspicious day today.

2:07:17.125 --> 2:07:18.000
I haven't had a bath.

2:07:18.625 --> 2:07:21.166
So what!
You're going to see our God, after all.

2:07:21.250 --> 2:07:22.208
Why do you need
cleanliness for that?

2:07:22.291 --> 2:07:23.625
God won't get angry, you go!

2:07:26.250 --> 2:07:27.250
Where is the bus stand?

2:07:29.083 --> 2:07:30.458
Where do you have to go?

2:07:31.083 --> 2:07:32.791
The bus that goes to Thiruvarur,
will not pass from here.

2:07:33.083 --> 2:07:34.708
It will come up to Anna's statue
and then take a turn.

2:07:34.875 --> 2:07:38.500
I need to go to Madras.
Actually, any place is fine,

2:07:39.416 --> 2:07:40.333
I just need to leave from here.

2:07:41.375 --> 2:07:44.250
Every ten minutes, there is a bus
to Thanjavur. It will stop here.

2:07:44.375 --> 2:07:45.791
-But…
-Thanjavur works.

2:07:56.833 --> 2:07:58.041
Can you do me a favor?

2:07:58.958 --> 2:08:02.208
When you go inside the temple,
just take a few flowers and…

2:08:02.333 --> 2:08:03.333
You want me to do an offering?

2:08:03.416 --> 2:08:04.291
Yes.

2:08:04.541 --> 2:08:05.375
In whose name?

2:08:10.666 --> 2:08:11.583
I don't know the name.

2:08:13.458 --> 2:08:14.625
Do it in the name of God.

2:08:23.125 --> 2:08:23.958
Brother,

2:08:24.875 --> 2:08:26.833
till the bus comes,
why don't you sit here?

2:08:26.958 --> 2:08:27.791
It's alright.

2:08:48.958 --> 2:08:50.250
Will you have tea, brother?

2:08:50.958 --> 2:08:52.083
-No.
-Why not?

2:08:53.666 --> 2:08:54.500
The bus will come.

2:08:54.750 --> 2:08:57.000
So what?
You can go on the next bus.

2:08:59.083 --> 2:08:59.958
I haven't brushed my teeth.

2:09:02.583 --> 2:09:03.541
So you haven't
brushed your teeth.

2:09:04.875 --> 2:09:06.791
Without even brushing your teeth,
or taking a bath,

2:09:07.250 --> 2:09:09.166
why are you in a hurry
to go to Madras?

2:09:56.791 --> 2:09:57.625
Hey!

2:09:58.041 --> 2:09:59.750
When did you come?
You never called.

2:11:34.125 --> 2:11:35.333
What happened to you, Arul?

2:11:36.583 --> 2:11:38.666
You don't seem alright
ever since you came back.

2:11:39.958 --> 2:11:41.166
Did something happen there?

2:11:47.416 --> 2:11:49.041
What happened to you, tell me?

2:11:53.083 --> 2:11:54.916
Hema, I told you I met
someone there, right?

2:11:55.541 --> 2:11:56.458
Yes.

2:11:57.583 --> 2:11:59.291
He was so affectionate towards me.

2:12:01.208 --> 2:12:03.958
Not just me, he's very
affectionate with everyone.

2:12:06.166 --> 2:12:08.916
He remembers incidents that
happened so many years ago.

2:12:11.333 --> 2:12:14.208
He worships the cycle that I gave
him unknowingly many years ago.

2:12:17.791 --> 2:12:19.916
He takes care of his bull
like his own child.

2:12:20.250 --> 2:12:21.666
He talks to everything…

2:12:22.583 --> 2:12:24.458
The fish in the sea,
the birds on the tree.

2:12:26.958 --> 2:12:30.125
He says he's going to name
his child after me.

2:12:31.916 --> 2:12:33.333
But I don't know his name.

2:12:35.666 --> 2:12:37.083
You call and talk to him, Arul.

2:12:37.166 --> 2:12:38.208
How can I even do that, Hema?

2:12:40.166 --> 2:12:41.041
He's right up here.

2:12:42.916 --> 2:12:45.875
But I saw him as a nuisance.

2:12:46.875 --> 2:12:49.750
He asked me for my mobile number.
I purposely gave him the wrong number.

2:12:52.208 --> 2:12:53.833
I didn't even ask for his name.

2:12:54.291 --> 2:12:55.291
I pretended like I knew him.

2:12:56.791 --> 2:12:58.041
Actually, he's up there,

2:12:59.125 --> 2:13:00.041
I am down here.

2:13:02.666 --> 2:13:04.916
I am feeling ashamed
to even call and apologize to him.

2:13:08.333 --> 2:13:09.208
Arul.

2:13:23.541 --> 2:13:24.458
Stretch.

2:13:43.958 --> 2:13:44.833
<i>Okay, uncle.</i>

2:13:45.750 --> 2:13:46.625
Okay, uncle.

2:13:46.958 --> 2:13:48.791
Not at all, uncle.
This itself is a huge favor.

2:13:51.375 --> 2:13:53.291
Uncle, six months is
the maximum time I'll take.

2:13:53.375 --> 2:13:54.666
But, I will return it before that.

2:13:56.041 --> 2:13:56.875
Okay, uncle.

2:13:57.250 --> 2:13:58.958
Thank you.
Thank you, Bye.

2:14:00.333 --> 2:14:01.166
All good?

2:14:01.500 --> 2:14:03.041
Just wait, this won't be enough.
We need more.

2:14:03.541 --> 2:14:04.583
Exactly how much do we need?

2:14:06.041 --> 2:14:07.208
We need another 25 lakhs.

2:14:13.458 --> 2:14:14.291
How much do you need?

2:14:14.375 --> 2:14:16.166
Sir, I need around 25 lakhs.

2:14:16.666 --> 2:14:17.500
When do you need it?

2:14:17.916 --> 2:14:20.250
Sir, whenever you give it, it's fine.

2:14:20.333 --> 2:14:22.166
Okay, as soon as possible.

2:14:23.583 --> 2:14:24.541
You will return it, right?

2:14:24.958 --> 2:14:25.875
What, sir!

2:14:27.041 --> 2:14:28.333
Just say you will return it!

2:14:29.083 --> 2:14:30.291
I'll surely return it, sir.

2:14:30.583 --> 2:14:34.333
Sorry, in fact, I did not want to ask you.

2:14:34.416 --> 2:14:37.625
Actually, you should say sorry
only for not buying a house till now.

2:14:38.000 --> 2:14:39.083
<i>I've asked you,</i>

2:14:39.166 --> 2:14:41.500
so many times why haven't
you bought a house yet.

2:14:42.166 --> 2:14:43.083
Yes, sir.

2:14:44.083 --> 2:14:45.416
Then, if not me,
who else will you ask?

2:14:45.708 --> 2:14:47.125
Okay, sir! Thank you, sir!

2:15:15.083 --> 2:15:17.000
Is this that "nameless" uncle's number?

2:15:18.291 --> 2:15:19.458
Why are you digging through that?

2:15:24.333 --> 2:15:28.166
Dad, please give me
your phone for a little while.

2:15:28.375 --> 2:15:29.416
Why?

2:15:30.083 --> 2:15:32.208
I want to call my friend.

2:15:34.000 --> 2:15:34.833
Here.

2:15:37.416 --> 2:15:38.500
Do you know the passcode?

2:15:38.750 --> 2:15:39.583
I know all that.

2:15:40.583 --> 2:15:41.583
Brat!

2:15:56.875 --> 2:15:58.375
Dad, there's a call!

2:15:59.166 --> 2:16:00.000
Who is it?

2:16:00.416 --> 2:16:01.375
I don't know, talk!

2:16:01.916 --> 2:16:02.791
Hello.

2:16:03.333 --> 2:16:04.250
<i>Live prosperously!</i>

2:16:04.375 --> 2:16:05.666
<i>Ezhil garments, tell me.</i>

2:16:08.666 --> 2:16:09.541
Talk!

2:16:11.875 --> 2:16:15.416
Hello, I am Arul, from Madras.

2:16:16.250 --> 2:16:17.083
<i>Athaan!</i>

2:16:17.666 --> 2:16:18.583
<i>Athaan!</i>

2:16:18.750 --> 2:16:19.875
How are you, <i>Athaan?</i>

2:16:20.250 --> 2:16:22.125
Just five minutes ago,
I was talking about you.

2:16:22.291 --> 2:16:23.666
<i>You'll live for 95 years!</i>

2:16:24.166 --> 2:16:25.000
<i>Your watch, right?</i>

2:16:25.458 --> 2:16:27.708
You left it in the bathroom.
I've kept it safely.

2:16:28.000 --> 2:16:29.458
I have also kept
your slippers safely in a bag.

2:16:30.041 --> 2:16:33.000
<i>What is this, Athaan? You just left</i>
<i>in anger, without even telling us.</i>

2:16:33.750 --> 2:16:35.708
<i>It's my Fault. I told you</i>
<i>to sleep but I slept off!</i>

2:16:36.375 --> 2:16:37.833
As soon as I woke up, I called you.

2:16:38.166 --> 2:16:39.500
Someone else answered the call.

2:16:40.125 --> 2:16:41.583
I tried again,

2:16:42.333 --> 2:16:44.125
<i>but the same person answered,</i>
<i>yelled at me, and hung up.</i>

2:16:44.541 --> 2:16:45.750
Then I asked Sokku uncle.

2:16:46.250 --> 2:16:47.125
He just shut me up, saying,

2:16:47.291 --> 2:16:48.458
"Stop troubling him.

2:16:48.583 --> 2:16:49.458
Is he a baby?

2:16:49.625 --> 2:16:51.208
Won't he know to go back himself?"

2:16:52.250 --> 2:16:54.041
I felt that I really troubled you.

2:16:55.791 --> 2:16:56.916
Whose number is this, <i>Athaan?</i>

2:16:58.541 --> 2:16:59.416
This is my number.

2:17:00.375 --> 2:17:01.333
How are you?

2:17:01.666 --> 2:17:02.958
Me? I am perfectly fine.

2:17:03.208 --> 2:17:04.208
So whose number is that?

2:17:05.541 --> 2:17:06.625
That…

2:17:07.750 --> 2:17:08.916
I gave you the wrong number.

2:17:09.375 --> 2:17:11.166
How can you go wrong
with your own number?

2:17:11.500 --> 2:17:13.500
I must have noted it down wrongly
since I was excited about the food.

2:17:15.833 --> 2:17:17.916
Actually, I want to ask you something.

2:17:18.541 --> 2:17:19.375
Tell me.

2:17:20.916 --> 2:17:22.166
I should have asked you
at Needamangalam, itself.

2:17:22.250 --> 2:17:23.125
But couldn't.

2:17:23.541 --> 2:17:25.916
I thought of asking you after coming here.

2:17:26.000 --> 2:17:30.541
But there was an emergency situation,
So, I had to arrange something.

2:17:31.583 --> 2:17:33.416
That's why I couldn't call earlier.

2:17:34.083 --> 2:17:35.083
Have you made arrangements?

2:17:37.458 --> 2:17:41.250
Sokku uncle told me that
you were in need of money,

2:17:41.416 --> 2:17:42.833
and you're running
around trying to arrange it.

2:17:42.916 --> 2:17:44.000
Have you made arrangements?

2:17:44.750 --> 2:17:46.458
Why did he tell you?

2:17:48.625 --> 2:17:49.833
I am not talking about that.

2:17:50.500 --> 2:17:52.791
<i>Athaan,</i> is everyone fine at home?

2:17:53.375 --> 2:17:54.291
No one's in trouble, right?

2:17:55.000 --> 2:17:57.250
No, no, everyone's fine.
It's not that kind of an emergency.

2:17:57.500 --> 2:18:01.125
We are trying to buy
the house we are currently residing in.

2:18:01.208 --> 2:18:03.583
I was busy making
arrangements for that.

2:18:04.166 --> 2:18:07.208
Thank god! I got worried
that it was something serious.

2:18:07.416 --> 2:18:09.625
To buy a house?
This is good news.

2:18:10.000 --> 2:18:11.916
When Sokku uncle told me,
I calculated and checked, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:18:12.000 --> 2:18:13.666
I have 15 lakhs in cash ready with me.

2:18:15.041 --> 2:18:15.875
Look,

2:18:15.958 --> 2:18:18.000
I want to talk to you
about something else.

2:18:18.250 --> 2:18:19.416
It's definitely not about the money.

2:18:19.625 --> 2:18:22.083
Why? You can't call
and ask me for money?

2:18:22.250 --> 2:18:23.750
Then how will I repay for
all that you've done for me?

2:18:23.916 --> 2:18:25.375
When you gave us, didn't we take it?

2:18:25.458 --> 2:18:26.625
Now when we are giving it,
you should take it!

2:18:29.458 --> 2:18:30.291
See,

2:18:30.625 --> 2:18:32.541
I have 15 lakhs in cash ready with me.

2:18:32.750 --> 2:18:34.083
If we pledge the jewelry
we have in the bank…

2:18:34.166 --> 2:18:35.958
Don't pledge the jewelry,

2:18:36.041 --> 2:18:37.791
I am telling you I don't even
want the money and you're…

2:18:37.875 --> 2:18:39.791
Relax, <i>Athaan,</i> allow me to speak!

2:18:39.875 --> 2:18:41.791
Your sister is the one who
suggested we pledge the jewelry.

2:18:42.333 --> 2:18:44.583
If we pledge the jewelry in the bank,
we will get around five lakhs.

2:18:44.833 --> 2:18:47.083
For the balance five,
I can ask the chit-fund guys.

2:18:47.166 --> 2:18:48.666
If we tell them we require
it for an emergency,

2:18:48.750 --> 2:18:49.750
they will immediately give it.

2:18:49.958 --> 2:18:53.916
So, five and another five make it 25.
Is 25 enough, <i>Athaan?</i>

2:18:54.583 --> 2:18:57.333
<i>Athaan,</i> we can even ask for a loan
from the co-operative society.

2:18:58.375 --> 2:18:59.333
Thanks a lot.

2:18:59.791 --> 2:19:02.458
But I don't need it. I've already made
arrangements. Now just listen to me.

2:19:02.708 --> 2:19:04.666
After telling you all this, if you
still don't take the money from me,

2:19:04.750 --> 2:19:06.333
I'll never speak to you again.

2:19:08.041 --> 2:19:08.958
Okay, I'll take it.

2:19:10.875 --> 2:19:11.958
Now will you allow me to talk?

2:19:12.833 --> 2:19:13.750
Okay, tell me.

2:19:21.000 --> 2:19:21.958
I…

2:19:22.916 --> 2:19:23.791
You…

2:19:28.583 --> 2:19:30.208
I don't know where to start.

2:19:31.208 --> 2:19:32.125
What, <i>Athaan?</i>

2:19:33.791 --> 2:19:35.458
I gave you the wrong phone number.

2:19:37.541 --> 2:19:38.541
Wrong number?

2:19:39.708 --> 2:19:43.041
I purposely gave
you the wrong number.

2:19:43.583 --> 2:19:44.416
Why, <i>Athaan?</i>

2:19:46.250 --> 2:19:47.583
I don't know you.

2:19:48.875 --> 2:19:50.208
I don't know your name.

2:19:51.791 --> 2:19:54.000
I was thinking, "Why should I give
my number to a stranger?"

2:19:56.875 --> 2:19:57.958
That's why I gave the wrong one.

2:20:02.500 --> 2:20:03.375
Hello!

2:20:05.666 --> 2:20:06.541
Can you hear me?

2:20:06.791 --> 2:20:07.750
I can hear you, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:20:11.291 --> 2:20:12.708
Even now I don't know who you are.

2:20:15.666 --> 2:20:18.375
You went on calling me <i>Athaan</i>
with affection and a sense of belonging,

2:20:21.125 --> 2:20:22.166
I couldn't tell you…

2:20:22.500 --> 2:20:24.458
that… I don't know you.

2:20:25.708 --> 2:20:26.666
I just couldn't ask you.

2:20:28.333 --> 2:20:29.541
<i>Moreover, you were</i>
<i>with me all the time.</i>

2:20:31.916 --> 2:20:33.250
<i>So, I couldn't ask</i>
<i>anyone else as well.</i>

2:20:35.750 --> 2:20:38.333
An entire night at your house,

2:20:39.541 --> 2:20:41.333
without knowing who you were…

2:20:44.375 --> 2:20:45.583
I felt really bad.

2:20:49.083 --> 2:20:50.666
Like I had committed a big mistake.

2:20:53.375 --> 2:20:54.291
It definitely is…

2:20:56.541 --> 2:20:57.416
a big mistake.

2:21:01.250 --> 2:21:02.708
I managed to some extent,

2:21:06.583 --> 2:21:08.708
<i>but when you said you're going</i>
<i>to name your child after me,</i>

2:21:09.958 --> 2:21:11.708
And you said the next
morning I have to call

2:21:12.625 --> 2:21:14.791
all three of you by your
names and bless you…

2:21:15.333 --> 2:21:16.458
I froze!

2:21:21.833 --> 2:21:23.416
I couldn't handle your love,

2:21:25.375 --> 2:21:27.208
that's why without
even telling you,

2:21:28.333 --> 2:21:29.333
I ran away from the house.

2:21:33.375 --> 2:21:35.166
You, really don't know
who I am, <i>Athaan?</i>

2:21:38.750 --> 2:21:40.416
I may not know your name,

2:21:41.625 --> 2:21:43.416
I may have forgotten
how I am related to you,

2:21:45.625 --> 2:21:47.291
but I know who the real you is.

2:21:48.500 --> 2:21:49.375
<i>Forget that,</i>

2:21:51.333 --> 2:21:53.291
I figured out who I am
only because of you.

2:21:55.208 --> 2:21:56.083
This is the truth.

2:22:08.708 --> 2:22:10.041
Even now you don't know, <i>Athaan?</i>

2:22:13.750 --> 2:22:14.625
I don't know.

2:22:16.916 --> 2:22:17.791
Please forgive me.

2:22:18.666 --> 2:22:19.750
Don't say all that, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:22:21.791 --> 2:22:23.625
Just a minute, just a minute, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:22:31.375 --> 2:22:32.208
Hello!

2:22:35.208 --> 2:22:36.083
Hey!

2:22:36.916 --> 2:22:37.791
Are you crying?

2:22:42.708 --> 2:22:43.666
Forget it, it's alright.

2:22:45.250 --> 2:22:46.666
I made a huge mistake,

2:22:48.041 --> 2:22:48.958
forgive me.

2:22:50.416 --> 2:22:51.791
Don't say all that, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:22:52.583 --> 2:22:54.500
At least now you
felt like finding out.

2:22:55.583 --> 2:22:56.416
Do you really want to?

2:22:58.125 --> 2:22:59.583
I feel like hearing it from you.

2:22:59.958 --> 2:23:02.500
You might be busy,
let's talk later, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:23:03.583 --> 2:23:05.291
There is no work more
important than this.

2:23:05.833 --> 2:23:06.916
Please tell me.

2:23:07.666 --> 2:23:08.875
Tell me, you have forgiven me.

2:23:09.333 --> 2:23:10.208
I'll tell you that,

2:23:10.541 --> 2:23:13.083
but you should promise
to come here again and see me.

2:23:15.166 --> 2:23:17.541
I promise I'll come, dear.
I'll come tomorrow itself.

2:23:18.041 --> 2:23:19.416
Please tell me
you've forgiven me.

2:23:20.000 --> 2:23:21.750
Don't say such big words, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:23:23.083 --> 2:23:24.333
I might just die.

2:23:25.583 --> 2:23:26.833
Just say you've forgiven me.

2:23:27.333 --> 2:23:29.125
You too forgive me, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:23:29.750 --> 2:23:30.625
Why?

2:23:31.000 --> 2:23:32.958
I knew that the bus which
was going to Chennai,

2:23:33.791 --> 2:23:35.708
was leaving at 09:00 p.m., <i>Athaan.</i>

2:23:36.625 --> 2:23:37.666
Despite that,

2:23:38.125 --> 2:23:40.791
if you had left then, I wasn't sure
when you would come again.

2:23:41.625 --> 2:23:43.833
I wanted you to see
Bhuvana's wedding

2:23:44.208 --> 2:23:46.666
<i>and wished for you</i>
<i>to stay with me for a day.</i>

2:23:47.375 --> 2:23:48.750
<i>So what was to be 09:00 p.m.,</i>

2:23:49.625 --> 2:23:52.375
I made it 10:00 p.m.
I told you a tiny lie, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:23:53.041 --> 2:23:54.250
It wasn't planned, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:23:54.333 --> 2:23:55.250
At that moment…

2:23:56.375 --> 2:23:57.250
Hey!

2:23:58.500 --> 2:24:01.583
You can lie about your phone number,
can't I lie about the bus timing?

2:24:01.666 --> 2:24:03.041
Why one set of rules for you
and another set of rules for me?

2:24:03.375 --> 2:24:04.458
Now it's fair and square.

2:24:04.541 --> 2:24:05.583
I'll also forgive you.

2:24:06.208 --> 2:24:07.791
Okay, I will spare you.

2:24:08.666 --> 2:24:09.666
Now tell me your name.

2:24:11.958 --> 2:24:12.916
Do you remember…

2:24:13.375 --> 2:24:15.291
your summer holidays of '94?

2:24:15.458 --> 2:24:16.500
Your tenth-grade vacation?

2:24:17.541 --> 2:24:19.458
I don't remember anything
much about the past.

2:24:19.625 --> 2:24:21.208
But you go on,
I may remember as you narrate.

2:24:21.750 --> 2:24:25.541
Okay, I'll come to that later.
First, I'll tell you who I am.

2:24:25.875 --> 2:24:26.708
Okay.

2:24:27.916 --> 2:24:29.250
I am no big star like
Rajinikanth or Kamal Haasan,

2:24:29.333 --> 2:24:30.666
to tell you about myself in one word.

2:24:30.750 --> 2:24:32.791
It will be slightly elaborate,
is that okay?

2:24:33.041 --> 2:24:34.041
Okay, now just tell me!

2:24:35.375 --> 2:24:36.958
Your mother's mother,

2:24:37.375 --> 2:24:38.750
who is from Kumbakonam,

2:24:39.125 --> 2:24:41.333
was born with three siblings.

2:24:42.333 --> 2:24:43.166
Hello!

2:24:43.750 --> 2:24:44.833
I am listening.

2:24:45.083 --> 2:24:46.208
Make some sounds
of acknowledgment, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:24:46.500 --> 2:24:48.125
Only then will I have
the interest to narrate.

2:24:52.333 --> 2:24:56.625
So, your late great-grandparents,
Maruthamuthu and Jagadambal,

2:24:56.708 --> 2:24:57.958
had four children.

2:24:58.166 --> 2:25:01.166
Sivagnanam, Janagam, Gopu,
and Padma. Am I right?

2:25:03.125 --> 2:25:04.833
Janagam is your grandmother.

2:25:05.083 --> 2:25:07.833
Your mother, your uncle,
and all your aunts were born to her.

2:25:09.208 --> 2:25:10.333
Hey, I know all that.

2:25:10.458 --> 2:25:12.375
Wow! Not bad!

2:25:12.750 --> 2:25:15.333
So, Janagam granny's brother,
Sivagnanam grandpa,

2:25:15.458 --> 2:25:17.041
had four children.

2:25:17.416 --> 2:25:21.000
Paneerselvam, Angamma,
Banumathy and Vijayalakshmi.

2:25:21.291 --> 2:25:23.833
That Angamma is my mother.

2:25:25.125 --> 2:25:26.000
Superb.

2:25:26.458 --> 2:25:27.416
Now will you tell me your name?

2:25:27.625 --> 2:25:29.833
Wait! I've only told
you half of the story.

2:25:30.416 --> 2:25:32.083
Now let's start again from the beginning.

2:25:32.958 --> 2:25:36.333
Your mother's father,
as in, your grandfather's there, right?

2:25:37.458 --> 2:25:38.333
He "was" there.

2:25:39.041 --> 2:25:39.875
Is that so?

2:25:40.458 --> 2:25:43.166
Okay, your grandfather
was born with six siblings.

2:25:43.458 --> 2:25:44.666
One of them was Gurunathar.

2:25:45.166 --> 2:25:47.250
That Gurunathar had three kids.

2:25:47.500 --> 2:25:49.833
Santhanam, Kanakavalli,
and Loganathan.

2:25:50.250 --> 2:25:51.958
That Santhanam is my father.

2:25:52.625 --> 2:25:53.500
Okay.

2:25:53.875 --> 2:25:59.625
Your granny was the matchmaker
who got them married.

2:26:00.125 --> 2:26:01.000
Superb.

2:26:01.291 --> 2:26:03.375
My brother and I were born to them.

2:26:03.708 --> 2:26:05.250
Now at least you can
tell me your name, right?

2:26:05.708 --> 2:26:06.666
It's not like you'll lose anything!

2:26:07.083 --> 2:26:07.958
Wait, hang on!

2:26:08.125 --> 2:26:09.666
We are almost there,
just a little bit more to go.

2:26:10.291 --> 2:26:13.333
Now let's go back to '94.

2:26:16.833 --> 2:26:20.541
I can never forget that year
for many reasons, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:26:21.208 --> 2:26:23.500
<i>For the first time, we traveled</i>
<i>outside Needamangalam.</i>

2:26:23.750 --> 2:26:25.791
<i>For the first time, we had</i>
<i>gotten into an outstation bus.</i>

2:26:26.041 --> 2:26:29.083
<i>For the first time, we were</i>
<i>coming to Thanjavur to your house.</i>

2:26:29.666 --> 2:26:31.250
<i>All through the journey,</i>
<i>my father advised me,</i>

2:26:31.458 --> 2:26:34.500
<i>"You shouldn't shout, nor fight,</i>
<i>nor dig your nose,</i>

2:26:34.583 --> 2:26:36.250
<i>nor talk in the village dialect."</i>

2:26:36.333 --> 2:26:38.041
<i>He was laying down so many</i>
<i>conditions while coming there.</i>

2:26:38.500 --> 2:26:41.125
At that time, you had just finished
your tenth grade and were confused,

2:26:41.208 --> 2:26:44.291
about whether to join polytechnic college
or complete your 11th and 12th grade.

2:26:44.833 --> 2:26:47.041
<i>But you used to always call</i>
<i>me aside and talk to me.</i>

2:26:47.458 --> 2:26:49.291
<i>Wherever you went,</i>
<i>you took me along.</i>

2:26:50.583 --> 2:26:53.166
<i>You used to play with</i>
<i>us kids, at our level.</i>

2:26:53.958 --> 2:26:55.791
<i>You used to teach</i>
<i>us a lot of new things.</i>

2:26:57.041 --> 2:26:59.458
<i>You weren't like this then,</i>
<i>you used to always be cheerful.</i>

2:27:01.375 --> 2:27:03.125
You used to talk to everyone so kindly.

2:27:03.625 --> 2:27:05.291
I learned that from you, <i>Athaan.</i>

2:27:05.916 --> 2:27:06.916
Really?

2:27:07.583 --> 2:27:08.625
Was I like that?

2:27:09.291 --> 2:27:10.458
I swear on you!

2:27:10.666 --> 2:27:11.625
Oh, no! I believe you.

2:27:12.041 --> 2:27:12.916
See, finally,

2:27:13.375 --> 2:27:14.416
not just about you,

2:27:14.708 --> 2:27:16.583
but I have even found out
about myself from you.

2:27:20.916 --> 2:27:22.958
You're the one who first
took me to a cinema theater.

2:27:23.041 --> 2:27:25.958
<i>At Kumaran Cinema Theater, we saw the</i>
<i>matinee show of</i> Veetla Visheshanga.

2:27:26.125 --> 2:27:29.458
<i>Even though you had already</i>
<i>seen it, you took us again.</i>

2:27:30.166 --> 2:27:32.333
<i>How I wasn't tall enough and</i>
<i>used to keep adjusting to see the film.</i>

2:27:32.875 --> 2:27:35.416
<i>How you got us ice cream</i>
<i>and popcorn during the interval.</i>

2:27:35.708 --> 2:27:37.083
<i>The smell of the cinema theater,</i>

2:27:37.500 --> 2:27:38.916
<i>I can't forget anything, Athaan!</i>

2:27:40.041 --> 2:27:41.208
<i>Even now when I think about it…</i>

2:27:42.875 --> 2:27:45.208
But I am not able to figure out
whether I actually remember,

2:27:45.291 --> 2:27:47.083
or because you're narrating
I am imagining that I remember.

2:27:48.125 --> 2:27:50.541
Okay, listen, this is
the most important part.

2:27:50.833 --> 2:27:54.041
<i>There were eight of us, all small kids.</i>

2:27:54.458 --> 2:27:56.250
<i>Unable to manage</i>
<i>all of us at home…</i>

2:27:56.333 --> 2:27:59.333
<i>They sent us with you to the market.</i>

2:27:59.416 --> 2:28:01.166
<i>All of us would hold hands and follow you.</i>

2:28:01.291 --> 2:28:03.750
We used to compete amongst ourselves
to hold your hand.

2:28:06.125 --> 2:28:07.083
Okay.

2:28:07.458 --> 2:28:10.166
To keep us under control you used to
do something till we reached the shop,

2:28:10.250 --> 2:28:12.291
do you remember what that was?

2:28:12.791 --> 2:28:14.541
No, what was it?

2:28:14.708 --> 2:28:17.416
You'd name each one
of us after a vegetable.

2:28:17.958 --> 2:28:20.416
And till we reached the shop
we had to keep repeating,

2:28:20.500 --> 2:28:23.000
how much of that vegetable
we were going to buy.

2:28:23.083 --> 2:28:24.000
Cabbage, one kilo,

2:28:24.083 --> 2:28:26.375
-What vegetable are you?
-Potato, two kilos.

2:28:26.791 --> 2:28:27.708
The last one?

2:28:27.791 --> 2:28:29.333
Small Onion, three kilos.

2:28:35.458 --> 2:28:37.000
Green Chili for five rupees.

2:28:37.083 --> 2:28:38.166
Ladyfinger, one kilo.

2:28:38.250 --> 2:28:39.500
Like this, we would keep
repeating it and walking.

2:28:39.916 --> 2:28:40.875
In that group,

2:28:41.375 --> 2:28:43.791
Priya was the Green Chili,

2:28:44.000 --> 2:28:44.916
and Ganesh was?

2:28:45.666 --> 2:28:46.541
Beans!

2:28:46.750 --> 2:28:48.916
That's more like it!
You remember now.

2:28:49.000 --> 2:28:50.833
Meena's name was Big Onion.

2:28:50.916 --> 2:28:52.875
Ranji's name was Small Onion.

2:28:53.375 --> 2:28:55.250
Yes, Ramya was Ladyfinger,

2:28:55.708 --> 2:28:57.000
and Saravanan was Turkey Berry.

2:28:57.666 --> 2:28:58.625
Bhuvana? Balamurali?

2:28:59.958 --> 2:29:02.875
Bhuvana was Tomato, no,
Balamurali was Tomato.

2:29:03.250 --> 2:29:04.208
Bhuvana…

2:29:07.291 --> 2:29:08.208
Bhuvana…

2:29:08.291 --> 2:29:09.166
Shall I tell you?

2:29:09.500 --> 2:29:11.208
No, no, don't. I will remember it.

2:29:11.375 --> 2:29:12.666
Okay, countdown from one to five.

2:29:13.875 --> 2:29:15.083
One…

2:29:15.583 --> 2:29:17.291
-Wait.
<i>-Two.</i>

2:29:17.541 --> 2:29:20.041
-Bhuvana was…
<i>-Three.</i>

2:29:20.541 --> 2:29:21.625
Give me a clue.

2:29:21.791 --> 2:29:24.125
You can eat that as a vegetable
and as a fruit.

2:29:25.541 --> 2:29:26.500
Capsicum?

2:29:26.666 --> 2:29:28.958
Wrong. Four.

2:29:29.166 --> 2:29:30.541
<i>Four and one-fourth…</i>

2:29:30.958 --> 2:29:32.166
<i>Four and a half…</i>

2:29:32.416 --> 2:29:33.833
-Bhuvana…
<i>-Four and three-fourths…</i>

2:29:33.916 --> 2:29:35.666
Plantain! Bhuvana was Plantain.

2:29:35.833 --> 2:29:37.333
Superb, <i>Athaan!</i>

2:29:37.958 --> 2:29:39.250
Oh, man!

2:29:40.208 --> 2:29:41.416
Not done yet.

2:29:41.750 --> 2:29:42.875
Who was Cabbage?

2:29:43.666 --> 2:29:46.250
Wait, I know. Cabbage was…

2:29:47.083 --> 2:29:48.708
that person's son…

2:29:49.208 --> 2:29:50.750
I forgot his name.

2:29:52.250 --> 2:29:54.000
Come on, you're pretty close.

2:29:55.916 --> 2:29:58.166
That boy had a lovely name.

2:29:58.916 --> 2:30:00.166
He also had two whorls on his head.

2:30:00.458 --> 2:30:04.583
His name was Madhi… Madhi!

2:30:05.916 --> 2:30:06.875
Madhiyazhagan.

2:30:08.541 --> 2:30:10.625
Madhiyazhagan was Cabbage. Yes!

2:30:11.708 --> 2:30:12.791
I wonder how he is now.

2:30:13.208 --> 2:30:15.375
Nothing to worry about.
He's absolutely fine.

2:30:16.500 --> 2:30:18.500
You remember Cabbage,

2:30:18.833 --> 2:30:21.125
but you don't remember his
elder brother, Potato, right?

2:30:21.500 --> 2:30:22.416
You are so mean, <i>Athaan!</i>

2:30:35.458 --> 2:30:36.333
Hey!

2:30:37.333 --> 2:30:38.208
Potato!

2:30:40.416 --> 2:30:41.458
Hey! Potato!

2:30:43.500 --> 2:30:44.375
Is it you?

2:30:45.750 --> 2:30:46.666
Is it you?

2:30:48.208 --> 2:30:49.541
Finally!

2:30:49.958 --> 2:30:51.625
What a tube light you are, <i>Athaan!</i>

2:30:54.250 --> 2:30:55.541
Hey, Potato!

2:30:56.250 --> 2:30:58.625
That's me! Your Potato.

2:31:00.583 --> 2:31:01.916
How are you?

2:31:02.916 --> 2:31:04.666
Yeah, right! I am fine.

2:31:05.250 --> 2:31:09.125
After talking for so long, now
you're asking me how I am? How silly!

2:31:09.750 --> 2:31:11.291
Forgive me, forgive me!

2:31:11.875 --> 2:31:15.333
Okay, now tell me my name.
I'll forgive you.

2:31:16.000 --> 2:31:19.041
Potato, that's it.

2:31:19.875 --> 2:31:21.458
Look at how you are dodging even now!

2:31:21.916 --> 2:31:23.250
That's the name you gave me.

2:31:23.750 --> 2:31:25.458
I am asking you about
the name my parents gave me.

2:31:32.083 --> 2:31:34.250
I won't tell you.
You never made it easy either, right?

2:31:35.208 --> 2:31:36.250
Look how you prolonged it!

2:31:37.291 --> 2:31:38.958
You can only tell it if you know it!

2:31:40.041 --> 2:31:42.250
You remember my brother's name,

2:31:42.333 --> 2:31:43.833
but you don’t remember my name, do you?

2:31:44.250 --> 2:31:45.541
Who said I don't remember?

2:31:46.250 --> 2:31:47.541
It's been a minute since I remembered.

2:31:48.375 --> 2:31:49.500
Then behave yourself and tell me my name.

2:31:49.583 --> 2:31:50.583
If you don't, I won't give you money.

2:31:50.708 --> 2:31:51.666
Then don't.

2:31:51.750 --> 2:31:52.583
Did I ask you for it?

2:31:52.666 --> 2:31:53.708
You were the one who said you'd give.

2:31:54.000 --> 2:31:56.666
Yes, exactly. I will give it to you,
and you have to take it.

2:31:57.000 --> 2:31:59.291
That's my share for your house.
How can you refuse it?

2:31:59.416 --> 2:32:00.500
Okay, give it.

2:32:01.125 --> 2:32:01.958
I'll take it.

2:32:02.041 --> 2:32:03.416
I'll take anything
you give me from now on.

2:32:03.708 --> 2:32:06.250
That's right! That's my <i>Athaan!</i>

2:32:06.625 --> 2:32:07.916
Okay, now tell me my name.

2:32:08.791 --> 2:32:09.666
I won't tell you now.

2:32:10.916 --> 2:32:11.833
If not now, then when?

2:32:13.166 --> 2:32:14.166
Later.

2:32:14.750 --> 2:32:15.708
When?

2:32:16.041 --> 2:32:16.958
Hey!

2:32:17.416 --> 2:32:20.375
I'll tell you!
Hang up, you Potato.

2:32:43.833 --> 2:32:44.750
NEEDAMANGALAM

2:32:57.708 --> 2:32:58.666
Come, brother.

2:32:58.916 --> 2:32:59.791
Do you remember me?

2:33:04.041 --> 2:33:04.958
Just do an offering.

2:33:05.125 --> 2:33:06.083
In God's name?

2:33:35.791 --> 2:33:36.708
Potato!

2:33:37.833 --> 2:33:38.875
Potato!

2:33:41.708 --> 2:33:42.666
Potato!

2:33:43.833 --> 2:33:44.750
Hey, Potato!

2:33:44.916 --> 2:33:45.833
Open the door.

2:33:49.000 --> 2:33:49.875
Hey!

2:33:50.208 --> 2:33:52.333
Enough now! I can't take it anymore!

2:33:52.791 --> 2:33:53.916
Open the door.

2:33:59.000 --> 2:34:00.541
I know you're on the other side
of the door.

2:34:01.833 --> 2:34:03.875
Hey! Don't torture me, rascal!

2:34:05.333 --> 2:34:06.291
Open the door!

2:34:10.125 --> 2:34:12.708
Open the door, Meiyazhagan!

2:34:25.375 --> 2:34:26.541
<i>Athaan!</i>
